Geography trivia is an exciting way to challenge your knowledge of the world. It’s time to brush up on your map skills, as you’ll have to think back to your high school and college classes for these geography trivia questions. Even if you don’t know the answer, it’s fun to take a guess and potentially learn something new. Students and geography-lovers of all levels will find these geography questions thrilling and fun and can in turn edify their knowledge of the planet.
What is the name of the tallest mountain in the world?:Mount Fansipan:Mount Everest:Godwin Austen:Cho Oyu:2:CON
Which country has the largest population in the world?:Russia:India:China:Brazil:3:CON
What is the name of the longest river in Africa?:The Ganges River:The Nile River:The Amazon:The Indus River:2:CON
What is the name of the smallest country in the world?:Vatican City:San Marino:Singapore:Monaco:1:CON
What is the name of the river that flows through the Brazil rainforest?:The Amazon:The Nile River:The Parana River:The Congo River:1:FINAL
